<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="77" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[810,1458,216,1677]" box="[813,917,216,242]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">FINDINGS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[810,1458,216,1677]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
The same taxon that was first described as 
<taxonomicName authority="Poir." authorityName="Poir. (Poiret" authorityYear="1804" box="[1243,1413,247,273]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis box="[1243,1357,247,273]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
Poir.
</taxonomicName>
was published again as 
<taxonomicName authority="L. H. Bailey (Bailey 1890: 719)" authorityName="L. H. Bailey (Bailey" authorityYear="1890" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="villosus" variety="sativus">
<emphasis box="[1017,1121,279,305]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. villosus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1173,1242,280,305]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">sativus</emphasis>
L.H. Bailey (
<bibRefCitation author="BAILEY L. H." pageId="12" pageNumber="77" pagination="719 - 723" refId="ref16118" refString="BAILEY L. H. 1890. - Notes from a garden herbarium 2. The American Garden 11: 719 - 723." type="journal article" year="1890">Bailey 1890: 719</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<typeStatus box="[938,1021,311,337]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">neotype</typeStatus>
designated here: BH 000 092 458 (
<figureCitation box="[1382,1439,311,338]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="13.[367,378,2008,2025]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,215,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-20@13.[203,1385,215,1915]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIG. 5. — Rubus sativus (L.H. Bailey) Clark neotype, L.H. Bailey (BH[BH 000 092 458]). Scale bar: 2 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4680788" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4680788/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">Fig.5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[810,1458,216,1677]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
As Bailey himself argued later (
<bibRefCitation author="BAILEY L. H." box="[1154,1384,343,370]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" pagination="507 - 590" refId="ref16357" refString="BAILEY L. H. 1944. - Rubus in North America. Eubatus. Alleghenienses. Gentes Herbarum 5: 507 - 590. https: // hdl. handle. net / 2027 / uc 1.31210001328085" type="journal article" year="1944">Bailey 1944: 512-514</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="BAILEY L. H." pageId="12" pageNumber="77" pagination="591 - 835" refId="ref16395" refString="BAILEY L. H. 1945. - Rubus in North America. Eubatus. Arguti. Gentes Herbarum 5: 591 - 835. https: // hdl. handle. net / 2027 / uc 1.31210001328085" type="journal article" year="1945">1945: 823</bibRefCitation>
), this is only a form of 
<taxonomicName box="[1108,1271,375,401]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="allegheniensis">
<emphasis box="[1108,1271,375,401]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. allegheniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as confirmed by the 
<typeStatus box="[855,900,407,433]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">type</typeStatus>
in Bailey’s herbarium. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. H. Bailey (Bailey" authorityYear="1890" box="[1148,1410,406,433]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="villosus" variety="sativus">
<emphasis box="[1148,1290,406,432]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">Rubus villosus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1343,1410,407,432]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">sativus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was raised to species rank by 
<bibRefCitation author="CLARK J. A." box="[1077,1273,438,465]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" pagination="151 - 188" refId="ref16851" refString="CLARK J. A. 1892. - Systematic and alphabetical index of new species of North American Phanerogams and Pteridophytes, published in 1891. Contributions from the United States National Herbarium 1: 151 - 188. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 368749" type="journal article" year="1892">Clark (1892: 159)</bibRefCitation>
; in the next year, she reconsidered her decision (
<bibRefCitation author="CLARK J. A." box="[1157,1346,470,497]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" pagination="258 - 264" refId="ref16902" refString="CLARK J. A. 1893. - Additions to the index for 1891. Contributions from the United States National Herbarium 1: 258 - 264. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 368857" type="journal article" year="1893">Clark 1893: 264</bibRefCitation>
), but this does not invalidate the earlier publication. 
<bibRefCitation author="KOEHNE E." pageId="12" pageNumber="77" refId="ref17931" refString="KOEHNE E. 1895. - Just's botanischer Jahresbericht. Systematisch geordnetes Repertorium der botanischen Literatur aller Lander 20.2. Borntrager, Berlin, 630 p." type="book" year="1895">Koehne (1895: 98)</bibRefCitation>
supported its treatment at the species level. Consequently 
<taxonomicName authority="(L. H. Bailey) Clark" authorityName="Clark" baseAuthorityName="L. H. Bailey" box="[812,1125,566,593]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sativus">
<emphasis box="[812,909,567,592]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. sativus</emphasis>
(L.H. Bailey) Clark
</taxonomicName>
is a later synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poir. (Poiret" authorityYear="1804" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and an earlier synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[1127,1289,598,624]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="allegheniensis">
<emphasis box="[1127,1289,598,624]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. allegheniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Because 
<bibRefCitation author="BAILEY L. H." pageId="12" pageNumber="77" refId="ref16166" refString="BAILEY L. H. 1898. - Sketch of the Evolution of our Native Fruits. MacMillan, New York, 465 p. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 19869" type="book" year="1898">Bailey (1898: 379)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. H. Bailey (Bailey" authorityYear="1890" box="[1046,1265,630,656]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="villosus" variety="sativus">
<emphasis box="[1046,1146,630,656]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. villosus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1198,1265,631,656]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">sativus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the protologue of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. H. Bailey" authorityYear="1898" box="[840,985,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nigrobaccus">
<emphasis box="[840,985,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. nigrobaccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the latter is typified by the 
<typeStatus box="[1280,1325,662,688]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1359,1455,662,687]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sativus">
<emphasis box="[1359,1455,662,687]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. sativus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and so it is a homotypic synonym of the latter (ICN, 
<bibRefCitation author="TURLAND N. J. &amp; WIERSEMA J. H. &amp; GREUTER W. &amp; HAWKSWORTH D. L. &amp; HERENDEEN P. S. &amp; KNAPP S. &amp; KUSBER W. - H. &amp; LI D. - Z. &amp; MARHOLD K. &amp; MAY T. W. &amp; MCNEILL J. &amp; MONRO A. M. &amp; PRADO J. &amp; PRICE M. J. &amp; SMITH G. F." pageId="12" pageNumber="77" pagination="159" refId="ref19323" refString="TURLAND N. J., WIERSEMA J. H. BARRIE, F. R., GREUTER W., HAWKSWORTH D. L., HERENDEEN P. S., KNAPP S., KUSBER W. - H., LI D. - Z., MARHOLD K., MAY T. W., MCNEILL J., MONRO A. M., PRADO J., PRICE M. J. &amp; SMITH G. F. (eds) 2018. - International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="journal article" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[813,861,725,751]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
: art. 
<geoCoordinate box="[971,1038,725,752]" degrees="52.2" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" precision="5555" value="52.2">52.2 e</geoCoordinate>
). The sequence of priority for the correct name is thus 
<taxonomicName authority="(Poiret 1804)" baseAuthorityName="Poiret" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[944,1204,757,784]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis box="[944,1057,757,783]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="POIRET J. L. M." box="[1073,1194,757,783]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" refId="ref18455" refString="POIRET J. L. M. 1804. - Encyclopedie methodique. Botanique. Vol. 6. Agasse, Paris, 786 p. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 824" type="book" year="1804">Poiret 1804</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Clark 1892)" baseAuthorityName="Clark" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1214,1449,757,784]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sativus">
<emphasis box="[1214,1308,758,783]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. sativus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="CLARK J. A." box="[1321,1440,757,783]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" pagination="151 - 188" refId="ref16851" refString="CLARK J. A. 1892. - Systematic and alphabetical index of new species of North American Phanerogams and Pteridophytes, published in 1891. Contributions from the United States National Herbarium 1: 151 - 188. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 368749" type="journal article" year="1892">Clark 1892</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Porter 1896)" baseAuthorityName="Porter" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[813,1133,789,816]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="allegheniensis">
<emphasis box="[813,978,789,815]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. allegheniensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="PORTER T. C." box="[995,1123,789,816]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" pagination="153" refId="ref18573" refString="PORTER T. C. 1896. - Rubus montanus Porter. Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club 23: 153. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 711534" type="journal article" year="1896">Porter 1896</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bailey 1898)" baseAuthorityName="Bailey" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[1147,1450,789,816]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nigrobaccus">
<emphasis box="[1147,1294,789,815]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. nigrobaccus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="BAILEY L. H." box="[1312,1439,789,815]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" refId="ref16166" refString="BAILEY L. H. 1898. - Sketch of the Evolution of our Native Fruits. MacMillan, New York, 465 p. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 19869" type="book" year="1898">Bailey 1898</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="BRAINERD E." box="[813,1018,821,848]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" pagination="23 - 29" refId="ref16765" refString="BRAINERD E. 1900. - The blackberries of New England. Rhodora 2: 23 - 29. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 560314" type="journal article" year="1900">Brainerd (1900: 26)</bibRefCitation>
used the name 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Clark" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1171,1264,822,847]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sativus">
<emphasis box="[1171,1264,822,847]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. sativus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for another taxon, but because he based his name on 
<taxonomicName authority="Bailey" authorityName="L. H. Bailey (Bailey" authorityYear="1890" box="[1166,1452,853,880]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="villosus" variety="sativus">
<emphasis box="[1166,1265,853,879]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. villosus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1313,1380,854,879]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">sativus</emphasis>
Bailey
</taxonomicName>
, this name is merely an isonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(L. H. Bailey) Clark." authorityName="Clark." baseAuthorityName="L. H. Bailey" box="[1149,1456,885,912]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sativus">
<emphasis box="[1149,1242,886,911]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. sativus</emphasis>
(L.H. Bailey) Clark.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[810,1458,216,1677]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
The history of the name can be summarized as follows: a plant from North America was planted in Kew Gardens in 1777 (
<bibRefCitation author="AITON W. T." box="[885,1071,980,1007]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" refId="ref15967" refString="AITON W. T. 1811. - Hortus Kewensis or a Catalogue of Plants Cultivated in the Royal Botanic Garden at Kew. Vol. 3. 2 nd ed. Longman etc., London, 432 p. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 105339" type="book" year="1811">Aiton 1811: 269</bibRefCitation>
). It was named (but not published) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aiton (Aiton" authorityYear="1789" box="[813,957,1012,1038]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis box="[813,957,1012,1038]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">Rubus villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Solander. A piece was dried and conserved in the herbarium at Kew, now in BM. A second collection was sent to De Candolle, which is now in G-DC. 
<bibRefCitation author="AITON W." pageId="12" pageNumber="77" refId="ref15920" refString="AITON W. 1789. - Hortus Kewensis or a Catalogue of Plants Cultivated in the Royal Botanic Garden at Kew. Vol. 2. Nicol, London, 460 p. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 4504" type="book" year="1789">Aiton (1789)</bibRefCitation>
formally published this species in the catalogue of Kew Gardens, based on the 
<typeStatus box="[1128,1174,1141,1167]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">type</typeStatus>
in Kew. French botanists in Paris incorrectly assumed that this species was the same as a plant in their botanical garden, which had been named (but not published) 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Poiret" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[1023,1139,1236,1262]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis box="[1023,1139,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Jussieu. Due to taxonomic doubt about its identity, Poiret published 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Poiret" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[1242,1357,1267,1293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis box="[1242,1357,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid name. However, this confusion continued in the work of later authors until Bailey consulted the 
<typeStatus box="[1194,1241,1332,1358]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">type</typeStatus>
in BM. He rightly concluded that the specimen belonged to a different section than that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Poiret" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[938,1053,1395,1421]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis box="[938,1053,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which, however, he recognized under the name 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Porter" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[922,1089,1427,1453]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="allegheniensis">
<emphasis box="[922,1089,1427,1453]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. allegheniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. That name has been in common use since the early 20TH century for the widespread highbush blackberry which is 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Poiret" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[1029,1147,1491,1517]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis box="[1029,1147,1491,1517]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[810,1458,216,1677]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
The identity of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aiton (Aiton" authorityYear="1789" box="[1018,1128,1523,1549]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis box="[1018,1128,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remained obscure and often is considered irrelevant because it is an illegitimate, later homonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Thunb. Its" authorityName="Thunb. Its" box="[961,1184,1586,1613]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis box="[961,1064,1586,1612]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. villosus</emphasis>
Thunb. Its
</taxonomicName>
valid replacement name, 
<taxonomicName authority="J. F. Gmel." authorityName="J. F. Gmel. (Gmelin" authorityYear="1791" box="[813,1037,1618,1645]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serratus">
<emphasis box="[813,919,1619,1644]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. serratus</emphasis>
J.F. Gmel.
</taxonomicName>
, has long been neglected but now must replace the later synonym, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. H. Bailey, Gentes Herbarum" authorityYear="1943" box="[1102,1220,1650,1676]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leviculus">
<emphasis box="[1102,1220,1650,1676]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. leviculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
